MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: Where_ancient_warlords_sleep_alone
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 171
  mythName: Where ancient warlords sleep alone
  omens:
  - 1. A breeze with the scent of steel and blood.
  - '2. A dancing farmer is herding her geese and

    dragging a skeletal corpse
    wrapped in

    cloth. She gladly explains that she''s

    taking her grandfather
    to the Rock, the

    only resting place for such a warrior.'
  - '3. A Knight of white stone stands guarding

    a withered tree, just a few
    pieces of fruit

    on its branches (see opposite). He explains

    that this
    fruit is being kept for warriors

    returning from the Rock. Punishments for

    eating
    the fruit can be lifted by a Seer.'
  - '4. A band of nine pilgrims seek the Rock.

    They offer protective talismans
    to

    Knights. These will ensure that warriors

    returning from the Rock
    do not mistake

    the Knights for enemies of the Realm.'
  - '5. An invigorating storm. With each flash of

    lightning the sound of battle
    can be heard.'
  - '6. Mist rolls back from a lake, revealing a

    rocky island within, a rowboat
    on the

    shore. Three bellowing warbands of

    warriors, waiting in death,
    ready to serve

    the Realm in battle one last time.'
  verse: 'Omens

    1. A breeze with the scent of steel and blood.

    2. A dancing
    farmer is herding her geese and

    dragging a skeletal corpse wrapped in

    cloth.
    She gladly explains that she''s

    taking her grandfather to the Rock, the

    only
    resting place for such a warrior.

    3. A Knight of white stone stands guarding

    a
    withered tree, just a few pieces of fruit

    on its branches (see opposite).
    He explains

    that this fruit is being kept for warriors

    returning from
    the Rock. Punishments for

    eating the fruit can be lifted by a Seer.

    4.
    A band of nine pilgrims seek the Rock.

    They offer protective talismans to

    Knights.
    These will ensure that warriors

    returning from the Rock do not mistake

    the
    Knights for enemies of the Realm.

    5. An invigorating storm. With each flash
    of

    lightning the sound of battle can be heard.

    6. Mist rolls back from
    a lake, revealing a

    rocky island within, a rowboat on the

    shore. Three
    bellowing warbands of

    warriors, waiting in death, ready to serve

    the
    Realm in battle one last time.

    Cast

    Alabaster Knight, Denebawde

    VIG
    15, CLA 8, SPI 8, 4 GD

    A4 (body of white stone)

    Black stone greatsword
    (3d10 slow)

    Wears a white python that whispers shrewd

    guidance, but
    cannot bite or cause harm.

    Rock Pilgrims, led by Marik

    VIG 10, CLA
    10, SPI 13, 2 GD

    Red cloaks, sacks of weapons intended as

    offerings
    to the warriors of the Rock

    Warriors of the Rock, led by Olthiar

    VIG
    16, CLA 10, SPI 16, 8 GD

    A2 (ancient mail, helm)

    Sword of extinct metal
    (2d8 long)

    Want to fight in a worthy battle. Can Smite.

    Amid the waves
    a stony throne'
  castEntries:
  - name: Alabaster Knight, Denebawde
    statBlock: 'VIG 15, CLA 8, SPI 8, 4 GD

      A4 (body of white stone)'
    notes: 'Black stone greatsword (3d10 slow)

      Wears a white python that whispers
      shrewd

      guidance, but cannot bite or cause harm.'
  - name: Rock Pilgrims, led by Marik
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 10, SPI 13, 2 GD

      Red cloaks, sacks of weapons
      intended as'
    notes: offerings to the warriors of the Rock
  - name: Warriors of the Rock, led by Olthiar
    statBlock: 'VIG 16, CLA 10, SPI 16, 8 GD

      A2 (ancient mail, helm)'
    notes: 'Sword of extinct metal (2d8 long)

      Want to fight in a worthy battle.
      Can Smite.

      Amid the waves a stony throne

      Where ancient warlords
      sleep alone

      SACRED FRUIT

      Type Punishment if Eaten

      1 Silver
      berries Turn to stone

      2 Bright oranges Voice silenced

      3 Translucent
      grapes Loss of eyes

      4 Purple pears A hand withers away

      5 Star
      figs Ghoulish face

      6 Huge peaches Become Exposed

      Rock

      Dwelling:
      Philosopher tower ~ Sanctum: Soothing thunder ~ Monument: Quiet flame

      Hazard:
      Magma field ~ Curse: Drizzle veil ~ Ruin: Defiled catacomb

      Th'
  flavorTable:
    title: SACRED FRUIT
    rows:
    - 1 Silver berries Turn to stone
    - 2 Bright oranges Voice silenced
    - 3 Translucent grapes Loss of eyes
    - 4 Purple pears A hand withers away
    - 5 Star figs Ghoulish face
    - '6 Huge peaches Become Exposed

      Rock'
  dwelling: Philosopher tower
  sanctum: Soothing thunder
  monument: Quiet flame
  hazard: Magma field
  curse: Drizzle veil
  ruin: Defiled catacomb
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
